{quote}
I've found one thing that DOES work. I'm not suggesting that this is the fix, but it does seem to give the desired behavior, at least for this test case. In URI::GetURIString(), m_path is escaped using URLEncodePathRFC3986() which explicitly checks for and does not percent encode the "=". If this call is replaced with a similar one that does escape the "=" (and only done here. URLEncodePathRFC3986() is called in a few places), the resulting URL becomes this:
{quote}

